<item>
            <title>[LU-12478] RHEL8 packaging</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12478</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;At make rpms there are a couple for quirks for the current RHEL8 release.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The new package dependencies are a bit too &apos;magical&apos; in that the new package that brings in kmodtool and defines&#160;kernel_module_package_buildreqs isn&apos;t very obvious.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Add enough fallback in the .spec file to &apos;BuildRequires:&#160;redhat-rpm-config kernel-rpm-macros kmod&apos; so on failing it becomes possible to bootstrap into a working RHEL8 environment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
